@Rick 

Alaska has a 645-mile straight line border on its eastern boundary with Canada running from the Arctic Ocean to the panhandle in the southeastern part of the state.  Since it is set to the 141st meridian west, it is indeed a straight line.  

Is it perfectly straight?  It looks that way on the map, but you'd probably need a surveyor to be sure. Since it is set to the 141st meridian west, it is indeed a straight line.

